HEADWORD: Rerefief
<hw>Rere"fief`</hw> <pr>(r?r"f?f`)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>arri⟦egrave⟧re-fief</ets>. See <er>Rear</er> hinder, and
<er>Fief</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Scots Law)</fld> <def>A fief held of a
superior feudatory; a fief held by an under tenant.</def>
<rj><au>Blackstone.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

